!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

centre /ˈsɛntə/

(centring,centred,centres) [英国英语] AM  center 

1. N-COUNT The centre of something is the middle of it. 中心 

例： A large, wooden table dominates the centre of the room. 一张大木桌占据了房间的中央。 

2. N-COUNT A centre is a building where people have meetings, take part in a particular activity, or get help of some kind. (会议、活动、援助的) 中心地点 

例： She now also does pottery classes at a community centre. 她现在还在社区中心上陶艺课。 

3. N-COUNT If an area or town is a centre for an industry or activity, that industry or activity is very important there. (行业、活动的) 中心; 中枢 

例： New York is also a major international financial centre. 纽约也是一个重要的国际金融中心。 

4. N-COUNT The centre of a town or city is the part where there are the most stores and businesses and where a lot of people come from other areas to work or shop. (镇、市的) 中心区 

例： ...the city centre. …市中心。 

5. N-COUNT If something or someone is at the centre of a situation, they are the most important thing or person involved. 居中心地位的人或物 

例： ...the man at the centre of the controversy. …处于争议中心的那位男子。 

6. N-SING If someone or something is the centre of attention or interest, people are giving them a lot of attention. (关注、兴趣的) 中心 

例： The rest of the cast was used to her being the centre of attention. 剧组的其他演员已经习惯了她成为众人关注的焦点。 

7. N-SING In politics, the centre refers to groups and their beliefs, when they are considered to be neither left-wing nor right-wing. 中间派 

例： The Democrats have become a party of the centre. 民主党人士已经变成一个中间派团体。 

8. V-T/V-I If something centres or is centred on a particular thing or person, that thing or person is the main subject of attention. 使集中; 集中 

例： ...the improvement was the result of a plan which centred on academic achievement and personal motivation. …该进步得益于一个强调学术成就和自我激励的方案。 

例： All his concerns were centred around himself rather than Rachel. 他所有心思都集中在他自己而非雷切尔的身上。 

9. -centered COMB in ADJ 以…为中心的 

例： ...a child-centred approach to teaching. …以孩子为中心的教学方法。 

10. V-T/V-I If an industry or event is centred in a place, or if it centres there, it takes place to the greatest extent there. 使集中; 集中 

例： The fighting has been centred around the town of Vucovar. 战斗集中在武科瓦尔镇进行。 

例： The disturbances have centred around the two main university areas. 骚乱集中发生在两所大学主校区。 

11.  →  see also community centre , shopping centre

